So scarcity is beginning to make its influence felt before it really
happens (Tabula Rasa)...

What this proto does is create a backdoor so we don't fell the
scarcity so much. Of course that's possible, but doesn't seem to be
the point to me.

Why not leave the pressure on? "Then minor bug fixes etc will never be
adopted", says Oerjan and stops his spring cleaning. But I'd like to
remind us that there are strategies to deal with scarcity that do not
rely on rule changes (which effectively abolish the scarcity again
before it begins to bite). 

Why not have a bit more wheeling and dealing connected to "minor",
uncontroversial proposals? For example, combining several of them in
one packet, until there are enough of them that they are worth the
three VTs they need (or until they begin to get controversial,
anyway...)? Oerjans spring cleaning certainly would produce such a
packet, and I'm not sure I'd just declare presence on it.

Kolja A.

