Re: DIS: BUS: Notes on newly expensive Proposal passage

Blob wrote:

>> >The reason I opposed it was that there would no longer be (and now there
>> >is not) any way to cheaply pass trivial fixes and public service Proposals
>> >that do not carry significant political interest.
>> 
>> Right.  It's time to make Disinterest meaningful again.

>I'm not so sure I know what all the fuss is about. It may cost 3 VTs 
>to pass a "trivial" proposal, but you get 2 VTs back as a reward for
>getting it passed. How much cheaper do you want it to be? If you made
>it Disinterested, so that you only had to spend 1 VT to pass it, and
>you waived the rewards, then you would not end up any better off. 
>When potential Zeitgeist rewards are added, you'd be better off not
>making your proposal Disinterested at all.

I don't think the fuss is about what it costs the proposer, but about
making it easy to get trivial but desireable proposals passed in spite of
Player reluctance to spend scarce votes.

>I also don't like the old Disinterest scheme because too many
>non-trivial proposal were being made Disinterested in order to make
>them easier to pass. If you really want to disambiguate between 
>"trivial" and "non-trivial" proposals, why not make it so that a 
>player can declare eir Proposal to be Disinterested Without Objection?
>If someone objects, then it must be taken that the proposal was not
>as uncontraversial as the author assumed.

This is a good point.  Attached is a revised Proto.

Proto: Real Disinterest

Amend Rule 1623 by appending the text:

      Any Player may cause a Disinterested Proposal to become
      Interested by posting a message to the Public Forum that
      unambiguously specifies which Proposal is to be made
      Interested, provided the message is sent no later than 48
      hours after the Proposal's distribution.

[Took Blob's suggestion to heart that all Players should agree if
a Proposal is really "trivial".  However, I made it a kind of
inverse "Without Objection" since this seems more natural to me.
Also limited the period of "objection" to give Players time to
assess the Proposal but not be able to force a transition at the
last minute.]

Amend Rule 955 by replacing the text:

                                                  and there were at
      least three votes in favor of the Proposal, then that Proposal
      is adopted.

with:

                                            and either there were at
      least three votes in favor of the Proposal or the Proposal was
      Disinterested, then that Proposal is adopted.

Amend Rule 947 by replacing the text:

      If a Proposal is adopted which

with:

      If an Interested Proposal is adopted which

Amend Rule 1786 by replacing the text:

      As soon as possible after a Proposal has been determined to
      have passed by the narrowest of margins,

with:

      As soon as possible after an Interested Proposal has been
      determined to have passed by the narrowest of margins,

[Comments:  Make sure Disinterested Proposals receive no rewards of any sort,
but make it possible to pass them with one vote.]

-- Crito


